# Password Generator

A secure, customizable password generator with REST API support and a React web interface.

## Table of Contents
- Introduction
- Features
- Tech Stack
- Installation
- Usage
- Project Structure
- License
- Author

## Introduction
This tool lets you generate random passwords with customizable length and character options. You can use it via a web interface or a simple REST API endpoint.

## Features
- Generate passwords with uppercase, lowercase, numbers, and symbols
- Choose password length (6–32 characters)
- Toggle inclusion of character types
- Access via REST API or web interface

## Tech Stack
- Backend: Node.js, Express (TypeScript)
- Frontend: React, TypeScript
- Deployment: Vercel (frontend), any Node.js host (backend)

## Installation
1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/Kash1shTyagi/Password-Generator.git
   cd Password-Generator
````

2. Install backend dependencies:

   ```bash
   cd backend
   npm install
   ```
3. Install frontend dependencies:

   ```bash
   cd ../frontend
   npm install
   ```

## Usage

1. Start the backend server:

   ```bash
   cd backend
   npm run dev
   ```
2. Start the frontend app:

   ```bash
   cd frontend
   npm start
   ```
3. Open your browser to `http://localhost:3000`

To use the API directly:

```
GET http://localhost:4000/api/generate?length=16&upper=true&lower=true&numbers=true&symbols=true
```

